@prof_nintendo I am so lost with the war between the factions at this point. I would love a modern installment just so we could see the effect the successes of past assassins had, but I doubt they'd do that because the history and mythology was popular and drew a lot of new players in I think
@matthewj19 Syndicate actually made me feel proud of being English 😂

@matthewj19 The last one I enjoyed was Syndicate but before that it was probably Brotherhood which was like the third major game ever released :/ if you're not massively into the Lore I'd say go for it! It still looks like a good game, just not a good AC game

@prof_nintendo Feels like we're given a character with a stealthy skillset and just expected to accept they've got some relation to the brotherhood, like TF isn't what they do in Valhalla the very reason Altair got stabbed and had to reform in the first place??

@prof_nintendo Exactly! If it didn't have the AC tag, I'd be all for it, but everything that makes me feel like part of a BROTHERHOOD is gone. I feel like the only consistencies now are the animus and the pieces of Eden.

There just seems to be this massive ludonarrative dissonance between the ideals of the brotherhood and gameplay in Valhalla. But lemme be clear if Ubisoft makes this work I will be so happy to be proven wrong and I will buy the shit out of this game
#AssassinsCreedValhalla

It could've had an extension of AC brotherhood's recruitment mechanic where you save people from 'bad' vikings and trained them and put them to work across the country, and add them to your settlement. I get we've seen like 30 minutes of gameplay and a trailer but :/

Like if they had incorporated a story element where Eivor disagreed with the brutish and reckless ways of her clan, and set out on her own path with the brotherhood to begin a new ethical, STEALTHY branch of viking that would've made some sense

I was really excited for Assassins Creed Valhalla but seeing the presentation today has me disappointed, and that's saying something because Norse mythology is an absolute favourite. I feel like any love I actually have for it is out of sheer loyalty to the early AC games
@prof_nintendo Agree! And what probably would've been a stealthy fortress infiltration is now a battering ram assault, I love the era but for the franchise.. Hmm
